BTG rises sharply after share split plan . Shares in BTG Plc , owner of a number of potentially lucrative patents , rose on Monday after the company said it would seek shareholder approval to split each of its 50p shares into five ordinary shares of 10p each . At 1015 GMT , the shares - - which have risen sharply in recent months on the back of hopes for its automotive and pharmaceutical products - - were up 37 - 1 / 2p at 25 . 50 stg . BTG , which announced a return to profitability in the six months to September 30 , said it remained cautious on profits for the whole year but said the split would improve marketability of the shares . BTG shares have been among the top performing UK stocks in recent months , having leapt from below 300p at the end of September 1995 . - - Brian Killen , London newsroom 44 171 542 7972 
